  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Weaning patients off ventilation in an ICU is sometimes difficult, because of three major
      inter-related etiologies: impaired lung, heart and diaphragm function. In this context,
      ultrasonography during tests to wean patients off ventilation could make it possible to
      diagnose cardiac dysfunction, a loss of pulmonary aeration or diaphragm dysfunction and thus
      reduce the number of failures at extubation.

      The study will be carried out in 100 patients on mechanical ventilation following abdominal
      or heart surgery, who will have echocardiography, and pulmonary and diaphragm
      ultrasonography.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
